        <div class="section_header">
          <div id="changes"></div>
                Guide For TinyHttp
        </div>
        <div class="content_section_text">
          <p>
          TinyHttp uses the GET/POST method to serve static content(text,HTML,GIF,and JPG..files) and to server dynaim content by running CGI program,which is in cgi-bin.TinyHttp provides following functions:<br>
        <b> 1.Provide GET and POST method to view static content and run CGI script</b><br>
        <b> 2.Provide HEAD and OPTIONS method </b><br>
        <b> 3.Provide Mechanism to handle multi-client </b><br>
        <b> 4.Provide Command Parameter to run the TinyHttp </b><br>
        <b> 5.Provide configuration file to run the TinyHttp </b><br>
        <b> 6.Provide dircetory view function </b><br>
        <b> 7.Provide easy logging function </b><br>
        <b> 8.Provide default file if not specify one </b><br>
        <b> and so on</b>
          <p>
                The system layout for an TinyHttp web server installation on Centos systems is as follows:
          </p>
          <pre>
/web/TinyHttp
|-- src 
|       `--  main.c
|       `--  log.c
|       `--  wrap.c
|       `--  parse_option.c
|       `--  parse_config.c
|-- include
|       |-- *.h
|       
|-- conf
|       `-- *.conf
|-- cgi-bin
|       `-- *.cgi
|--doc
|       `--  *.html *.jpg
|--log
|       `--  *.log
|--script
|       `--  *.sh
          </pre>
          <ul>
                        <li>
                           <tt>src:include all source code files</tt> 
                        </li>

                        <li>
                           <tt>include:include all head files</tt> 
                        </li>

                        <li>
                          conf:include config.ini file   
                           
                        </li>

                        <li>
                        cgi-bin:CGI script files

                        </li>

                        <li>
                        doc:include html ,text,JPG files
                        </li>
                        <li>
                        log:tiny.log
                        </li>
                        <li>
                        script:run.sh file
                        </li>
          </ul>
        </div>

